<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-02T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="599" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/965a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-02T18:00:00-05:00">October 2,
                                    1939—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1134. Please inform the British Government that in view of the suspension
                            of the obligations of the London Naval Treaty, 1936, by several other
                            parties to the treaty and in accordance with article 24, <pb facs="0573" n="561" xml:id="pg_561"/> this Government suspends so far as it is
                            concerned all the obligations of the treaty.</p>
                        <p>Request that notice to this effect be transmitted to the Governments of
                            Australia, New Zealand, and India.</p>
                        <p>Similar notice is being given to other parties to the treaty.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>